# Layout

Layout foundations define how content is structured and organized in Bioma interfaces.

## Grid System

Bioma uses a **12-column responsive grid** based on Bootstrap:

### Breakpoints

| Name | Width | Container Max Width |
|------|-------|---------------------|
| xs | menos de 576px | 100% |
| sm | ≥576px | 540px |
| md | ≥768px | 720px |
| lg | ≥992px | 960px |
| xl | ≥1200px | 1140px |
| xxl | ≥1400px | 1320px |

## Container

```html
<div class="container">
  <!-- Max-width container with responsive padding -->
</div>
```

## Responsive Utilities

Use spacing tokens with media queries:

```scss
.section {
  padding: var(--spacing-4);

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    padding: var(--spacing-6);
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    padding: var(--spacing-8);
  }
}
```

